<DATELINE>MONTPELIER, Vt. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 For years, Republican <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Jeffords </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Vermont </LOCATION>'s lone member of the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>, has enjoyed the backing of many state Democrats. Two years ago, he even won re-election with both the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> and Democratic nominations. This year, though, as <PERSON> Jeffords </PERSON> seeks the seat of retiring <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Sen. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Stafford </PERSON>, R-Vt., his popularity among Democrats is being used against him by <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> challenger <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffes </PERSON>, who calls himself the real Republican in the race <PERSON> Griffes </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jeffords </PERSON> will face off next Tuesday in <LOCATION> Vermont </LOCATION>'s Republican primary The winner will face Democrat <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Gray </PERSON>, a former <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> attorney, in the November election. <PERSON> Gray </PERSON> is unopposed in Tuesday's Democratic primary. <PERSON> Jeffords </PERSON> is the clear favorite in the primary, but his support of Democratic initiatives over the years has angered many of the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> faithful, including former four-term Gov. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Snelling </PERSON>, who donated $ 1,000 to the <PERSON> Griffes </PERSON> campaign. `` <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Jeffords </PERSON>, while he clearly has provided a long service to <LOCATION> Vermont </LOCATION>, has not, in my opinion, been very often mindful of the fact that he gets his nominations from the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>,'' said <PERSON> Snelling </PERSON>, himself considered a moderate to liberal. While <PERSON> Snelling </PERSON> was willing to give money to <PERSON> Griffes </PERSON>, he withheld his formal endorsement, saying the 35-year-ol