<DATELINE>MADISON, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Big spending has become a big issue in Tuesday's heated Democratic primary battle for the seat held for 31 years by retiring Sen. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Proxmire </PERSON>, whose last re-election campaign cost him $ 145.10. <ORGANIZATION> Milwaukee </ORGANIZATION> millionaire <PERSON> Herbert </PERSON> <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON>, running in his first election, stands accused of trying to buy the nomination by spending more than $ 2 million, much of it on TV advertising and much of it his own money. `` Politics should be people, ideas and leadership, not multimillion-dollar TV hype,'' said Secretary of <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Douglas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> La </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Follette </ORGANIZATION>, one of <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON>'s Democratic foes. <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> is one of six states holding primary elections Tuesday. <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON>, 53, owner of the <ORGANIZATION> Milwaukee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bucks </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Basketball </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, said he had to buy the ads to win the name recognition enjoyed by <PERSON> La </PERSON> <PERSON> Follette </PERSON>, former Gov. <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Earl </PERSON> and <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Garvey </PERSON>, who was the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> nominee two years ago. `` I'm not looking to get ahead of the other -LRB- candidates -RRB-,'' <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON> said. `` I just want to get to the point where we are even.'' On the Republican side, state <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Minority Leader <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Engeleiter </PERSON>, 36, and <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> B </PERSON>. King, 47, former chairman of the state <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZAT