<BYLINE>By THERESA HUMPHREY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Lt. Gov. S.B. Woo claimed victory today in <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> primary, saying state officials had discovered vote counting errors that he says reversed the results of the election. Challenger <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Beard </PERSON> had been declared the winner of Saturday's primary. Woo had conceded the race. <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hart </PERSON>, adminsitrative director of the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Elections </ORGANIZATION> for <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Castle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, said today a keypunch operator made a mistake that gave Beard 2,800 more votes than he received. `` When this correction is made, Woo will instead win by six votes,'' Woo said in a press release. But <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> said, `` I have no idea who is ahead.'' The unofficial tally had given Beard 22,418 votes to Woo's 19,624 The revised results would give Beard only 19,618 votes to Woo's 19,624. The final numbers, however, could change because votes from nine precincts still must be counted. Woo also said he believes additional absentee ballots will be counted. `` I have no idea how it happened, but I am satisfied in my own mind that it was human error,'' <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> said today. Beard campaign manager <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Siegel </PERSON> had no comment. `` <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> does n't think it is appropriate until the results are completed,'' he said. `` <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> wants to have the most accurate and clear count there is.'' The vote discrepancy came in the 23rd representative district in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Castle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, where there about 280 registered Democrats. In that district, however, Beard's total was tallied at 2,828 votes when he actually receiv