<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A huge bomb placed in a taxi blew up outside City Hall on Monday, injuring eight people who did not have enough time to flee after a telephoned warning, police said. Earlier Monday, two bombs set by guerrillas of the <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> badly damaged the home of Sir <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Bloomfield </PERSON>, head of <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>'s civil service. <PERSON> Bloomfield </PERSON>, 57, his wife and a son were not injured but were treated for shock. The blasts ripped holes in the brick house and shattered windows in neary homes. A third bomb near the house was defused by British army experts, police said. Police said that in <LOCATION> Armagh </LOCATION>, 35 miles southwest of <LOCATION> Belfast </LOCATION>, demolitions experts defused a 500-pound bomb found near the Drumsill Hotel. Press Association, <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s domestic news agency, said the <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> claimed responsibility for the blast outside <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hall </ORGANIZATION> that shattered shop and office windows over a large area of downtown <LOCATION> Belfast </LOCATION>. The agency did not say how it obtained its information on the claim of responsibility. Police said two of the injured were in serious condition. The outlawed <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> had carried out a car bombing on Aug. 24 only 150 yards from the site of Monday's blast. Last month's explosion caused more than $ 6.75 million in damage. In a statement, the <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> claimed responsibility for the <LOCATION> Bloomfield </LOCATION> house attack in <PERSON> Helen </PERSON>'s <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Down </LOCATION>, on the eastern outskirts of <LOCATION> Belfast </LOCATION>, and said other civil servants in <LOCATION> Northern </LOC