'' he said. Police swiftly sealed off the area to keep hundreds of people still leaving their offices from getting near the site, as shattered windows continued to drop shards of glass onto the sidewalks. British and <LOCATION> Irish </LOCATION> officials are scheduled to meet Tuesday under terms of the 1985 Anglo-Irish Agreement that give the <LOCATION> Irish </LOCATION> government a consultative role in the <LOCATION> British </LOCATION> province. The meeting was requested by Irish Prime Minister <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Haughey </PERSON> to discuss the worsening security situation.
