 `` Greatest Hits'' -LRB- RCA -RRB- _ The Judds On the back cover of this, their obligatory greatest-hits album, <PERSON> Naomi </PERSON> and <PERSON> Wynonna </PERSON> <PERSON> Judd </PERSON> tell us about `` the four shortest years of our lives,'' since they shopped their homemade demos around and landed themselves a record deal. No, it does n't seem like four years, but it has been. And this `` best-of'' package stands as testimony to the fact that The <ORGANIZATION> Judds </ORGANIZATION>, the much publicized red-headed mother-daughter duo, can no longer be taken as a novelty act or a curiosity. <PERSON> Naomi </PERSON> and <PERSON> Wynonna </PERSON> have made a harmonious place for themselves in 1980s country music. Nine of the 10 selections here have been released before on <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Judds </ORGANIZATION>' three studio albums. The big hits are present and accounted for: `` Why Not Me,'' `` Mama He's Crazy,'' `` Girls Night Out.'' `` Why Not Me'' opens the collection and sets the tone; it's a proud, no-nonsense song sung by two proud, no-nonsense women. The <ORGANIZATION> Judds </ORGANIZATION> know who they are, and they know what they want _ love, happiness, respect. The lone new track is their current hit, `` Give a Little Love,'' which continues their proud tradition with a bluesy, soulful approach. Like most greatest-hits packages, The <ORGANIZATION> Judds </ORGANIZATION> give old fans all their favorites in one place, while giving the uninitiated a freshman course in Judds 101. One minor complaint: They should have included their 1987 country cover of `` Do n't Be Cruel.'' <PERSON> Elvis </PERSON>, wherever he is these days, would have been proud. _ By <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Byrd </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
