<HEAD>US Sprint Operating Losses To Decline Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> US </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sprint </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communication </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s operating losses in the third quarter of 1988 should be sharply reduced from the $ 165 million it lost in the same period of last year and the $ 112 million lost in the second quarter of this year, <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Esrey </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telecommunications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> president and chief executive officer, said Monday. <PERSON> Esrey </PERSON> said that based on results in July and August, <LOCATION> US </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sprint </LOCATION> is expected to have pre-tax losses of no more than $ 35 million in the quarter ending Sept. 30. The long-distance telephone service is operated as a partnership of <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telecom </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>. They now own equal amounts, but <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telecom </ORGANIZATION> will purchase an additional 30.1 percent interest for more than $ 600 million in January 1989. <PERSON> Esrey </PERSON> said factors contributing to the improved performance were continued growth in net revenue and improved control of expenses. He said the correction of billing system problems which adversely affected results in previous periods was a major factor. Moving customer traffic from leased lines and microwave facilities onto <ORGANIZATION> US </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sprint </ORGANIZATION>'s new fiber-optics network also contributed to operating efficiency, he said. `` While much work remains to be done, we are very pleased with the recent progress we have made,'' <PERSON> Esrey </PERSON> said. `` <ORGANIZATION> US </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sprint </ORGANIZATION> is now in position to exceed our internal short-term objectives.''
