<HEAD>Board Of Trade Opposes Merc's Electronic Trading System</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> has urged regulators not to approve a rival commodities exchange's electronic network for 24-hour global trading of financial futures and options, on the grounds the system could lead to abuse and would be hard to operate. The <ORGANIZATION> CBOT </ORGANIZATION> sent a 51-page letter dated Sept. 6 to the <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trading </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> urging the commission to turn down the electronic venture, planned by the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Reuters </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>. The 12 -LCB- - year deal, which requires government approval, calls for the <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> network to begin operating next summer It would link investors in <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION> via an electronic system for trading futures and options contracts on currency futures, including the British pound, the West German mark, the Swiss franc, the Japanese yen and Eurodollar time deposits. The system would operate during hours when the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION>'s trading floor is closed. CBOT President <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Donovan </PERSON> raised a number of issues in the letter to the commission, ranging from the way contracts are normally traded in the pit to the possibility of fraud. `` The <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> proposal marks a complete departure from the centralized, open outcry markets which ensure the sort of honest and efficient price discovery which <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> has mandated,'' <PERSON> Donovan </PERSON> wrote in the letter. `` In effect, <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> is an off-exchange market. `` The <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> proposal is inherently susceptible to manipulation, prearranged trading and other abuses,'' his letter said. `` Moreover, the <ORGANIZATION> CME </ORGANIZATION>'s application is incomplete because it fails to address a variety of compliance, enforcement and liability issues including the applicability of foreign laws to the operation of <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> terminals located abroad. `` Finally, a host of unresolved financial and operational concerns, particularly in the wake of the October stock market decline, render final action on this unprecedented proposal altogether inappropriate,'' <PERSON> Donovan </PERSON> wrote. <ORGANIZATION> Reuters </ORGANIZATION>, the news and market information concern, will provide the technical expertise for <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION>. The Mercantile Exchange, a pioneer in the creation of financial futures and options, will provide the main market for the system. Futures and options allow investors to bet on the future performance of commoditiesm, currencies and financial instruments such as stocks and bonds.
</TEXT>
