<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> McCormick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Co.. <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> has sold its real estate holdings, amounting to about nine million square feet of office space, to the <ORGANIZATION> Rouse </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Company </ORGANIZATION> for $ 550 million, <PERSON> McCormick </PERSON> officials announced Monday <PERSON> McCormick </PERSON>, which held the real estate through its <ORGANIZATION> McCormick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Properties </ORGANIZATION>, has holdings in the <LOCATION> Baltimore-Washington </LOCATION> corridor, <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>. Appraisers valued <PERSON> McCormick </PERSON>'s real estate portfolio at $ 471 million last November, shortly before the company announced it planned to divest the holdings to concentrate on its food business. <PERSON> McCormick </PERSON> is the world's largest spice manufacturer, with 1987 sales of $ 1.1 billion. Rouse officials have indicated nearly all <ORGANIZATION> McCormick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Properties </ORGANIZATION> employees will be retained, said <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Lichtenauer </PERSON>, <PERSON> McCormick </PERSON>'s manager of marketing communications Rouse officials could not be reached for comment late Monday. <PERSON> Rouse </PERSON> holds about 2.4 million square feet of retail, office and industrial space, including <LOCATION> Baltimore </LOCATION>'s Harbor Place. The company purchased thousands of acres of farmland in the <LOCATION> Baltimore-Washington </LOCATION> corridor in the 1960s and designed the planned community of <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION>. A May report by <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Poors </ORGANIZATION> listed <ORGANIZATION> Rouse </ORGANIZATION>'s assets at $ 1.7 billion.
